==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Timbrel
<hw>Tim"brel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Dim. of OE.
<ets>timbre</ets>, OF. <ets>timbre</ets>; probably fr. L.
<ets>typmanum</ets>, Gr. <?/ a kettledrum, but influenced perhaps by Ar.
<ets>tabl</ets> a drum; cf. Per. <ets>tambal</ets> a drum. See
<er>Tympanum</er>, and cf. 2d <er>Timbre</er>, <er>Tymbal</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A kind of drum, tabor, or tabret, in use from the
highest antiquity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Miriam . . . took a <qex>timbrel</qex> in her hand, and all the
women went out after her with <qex>timbrels</qex> and with dances.</q>
<rj><qau>Ex. xv. 20.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Timbrelled</ent>⟦br⟧
